snippet.textDisplay:
pabuji was a king in Rajasthan is revered as folk deity...he is regarded as protector of animals....
once pabuji was getting ready for marriage sitting on female horse....but one person commented that the mare wasn't looking nice and suggested to go to charani....a local women who possessed a beautiful white mare....so pabuji went there to ask her mare....bu charani was reluctant to give her mare to pabuji as she loved her so much and also the female horse protected her cows and other valuable...
but when pabuji assured her that nothing will hapeen to cows as whenever charani felt any danger pabuji will be there to protect her animals.......so she was ready to give her mare to pabuji....
once in a while ....when she was in danger as some dakus (goons) attacked her cows... she sent some guy to call pabuji ....pabuji came to save her in mid of his marriage.  as hebhad only taken 3 feras (circle) and went to help charani...and saved her cows but died in the process.....so he is revered as protector of animals....till now rajputs only take 3 pheras in memory of him in marriage......😊
